item.description:
Most actions have several overloading methods for a table with composite keys, or a simple table with only partition key.
Get Most simple action to get an item from a table by key(s). Since return type U is only on the return type, all type parameters are required to be passed in explicitly.
def get[P: Encoder, S: Encoder, U: Decoder]( table: CompositeKeysTable[P, S], partitionKey: P, sortKey: S, consistentRead: Boolean ): F[Option[U]] Retrieve Similar to Get but can return multiple items by:
